{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869646628,"sessionID":"ses_285ebdaa6ffeX26M0sdERuF1ux","part":{"id":"prt_d7a1452510017X09X7KJz4Yaf7","messageID":"msg_d7a143e2f0017GYtC712NcPoqE","sessionID":"ses_285ebdaa6ffeX26M0sdERuF1ux","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_7f25dcb616ec43b3a055d331","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-028: SDK AgentRuntimeClient — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `sdk-python`\n6: - **Language:** Python\n7: - **Size:** M\n8: - **Base specs:** `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n9: \n10: ## Delta Requirements\n11: \n12: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeClient Initialization\n13: \n14: The system SHALL construct an `AgentRuntimeClient` that resolves configuration from arguments and environment variables, bootstraps a session ID via the data plane, and initializes the underlying `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`.\n15: \n16: #### Scenario: Constructor with all arguments\n17: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is constructed with explicit `agent_name`, `namespace`, `router_url`, `verbose`, `session_id`, `timeout`, and `connect_timeout`\n18: - **WHEN** the constructor completes\n19: - **THEN** all instance fields (`agent_name`, `namespace`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`, `logger`, `router_url`, `session_id`) SHALL be set to the provided values\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Constructor with defaults\n22: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is constructed with only `agent_name`\n23: - **WHEN** the constructor completes\n24: - **THEN** `namespace` SHALL default to `\"default\"`, `verbose` to `False`, `session_id` to `None`, `timeout` to `120`, and `connect_timeout` to `5.0`\n25: \n26: #### Scenario: Router URL from environment variable\n27: - **GIVEN** `router_url` is not provided as an argument\n28: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` runs\n29: - **THEN** it SHALL read `router_url` from the `ROUTER_URL` environment variable\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Router URL required\n32: - **GIVEN** neither `router_url` argument nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n33: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` runs\n34: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL` environment variable\n35: \n36: #### Scenario: Data plane client initialization\n37: - **GIVEN** valid `router_url`, `namespace`, and `agent_name`\n38: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` runs\n39: - **THEN** it SHALL construct an `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` with `router_url`, `namespace`, `agent_name`, `timeout`, and `connect_timeout`, storing it as `self.dp_client`\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: Session ID bootstrapping when not provided\n42: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is `None` or falsy\n43: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` runs\n44: - **THEN** it SHALL call `dp_client.bootstrap_session_id()` and assign the returned value to `self.session_id`\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: Bootstrap session ID missing header\n47: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is not provided\n48: - **WHEN** `dp_client.bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n49: - **AND** the response does not contain the `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n50: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` with message `Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id`\n51: \n52: #### Scenario: Session ID reuse when provided\n53: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is provided to the constructor\n54: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` runs\n55: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT call `bootstrap_session_id()` and SHALL use the provided `session_id` directly\n56: \n57: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeClient Context Manager\n58: \n59: The system SHALL support context manager protocol for `AgentRuntimeClient` to ensure proper resource cleanup on block exit.\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: Context manager entry\n62: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used in a `with` statement\n63: - **WHEN** `__enter__` is called\n64: - **THEN** it SHALL return `self`\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: Context manager exit with normal flow\n67: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager and the block completes without exception\n68: - **WHEN** `__exit__` is called with `exc_type=None`\n69: - **THEN** it SHALL call `close()` to clean up resources\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Context manager exit with exception\n72: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager and an exception occurs in the block\n73: - **WHEN** `__exit__` is called with exception info\n74: - **THEN** it SHALL call `close()` and SHALL NOT suppress the exception (return `None` or `False`)\n75: \n76: ### Requirement: Invoke Payload\n77: \n78: The system SHALL provide an `invoke` method to send JSON payloads to the Agent Runtime invocation endpoint and return the response.\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: Successful invocation\n81: - **GIVEN** a valid `session_id` is set on the client\n82: - **WHEN** `invoke(payload)` is called with a dictionary payload\n83: - **THEN** it SHALL call `dp_client.invoke(session_id, payload)` and return the `requests.Response` object\n84: \n85: #### Scenario: Invoke without session ID\n86: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is `None` or falsy on the client\n87: - **WHEN** `invoke(payload)` is called\n88: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n89: \n90: #### Scenario: Invoke with custom timeout\n91: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is valid\n92: - **WHEN** `invoke(payload, timeout=30.0)` is called\n93: - **THEN** the data plane invoke SHALL use `timeout=30.0` for the request\n94: \n95: #### Scenario: Invoke with default timeout\n96: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is valid and `timeout` argument is `None`\n97: - **WHEN** `invoke(payload)` is called\n98: - **THEN** the effective timeout SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` where `self.timeout` defaults to `120`\n99: \n100: #### Scenario: Invoke response handling\n101: - **GIVEN** a successful data plane response\n102: - **WHEN** `invoke` receives the response\n103: - **THEN** it SHALL return the response object without parsing (caller is responsible for JSON deserialization)\n104: \n105: ### Requirement: Close and Cleanup\n106: \n107: The system SHALL provide a `close` method to release the underlying HTTP session resources.\n108: \n109: #### Scenario: Close data plane session\n110: - **GIVEN** an initialized `AgentRuntimeClient` with a `dp_client`\n111: - **WHEN** `close()` is called\n112: - **THEN** it SHALL call `dp_client.close()` to close the underlying `requests.Session`\n113: \n114: #### Scenario: Close without initialized data plane\n115: - **GIVEN** `dp_client` is `None` or not set\n116: - **WHEN** `close()` is called\n117: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT raise an exception (no-op or safe guard)\n118: \n119: #### Scenario: Close idempotency\n120: - **GIVEN** `close()` is called multiple times\n121: - **WHEN** subsequent calls execute\n122: - **THEN** they SHALL NOT raise errors (safe to call repeatedly)\n123: \n124: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Bootstrap\n125: \n126: The system SHALL bootstrap a session ID by sending a GET request to the invocation base URL and reading the response header.\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Bootstrap session ID via GET\n129: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` instance\n130: - **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n131: - **THEN** it SHALL send `GET` to `self.base_url` and read the `x-agentcube-session-id` response header\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: Bootstrap returns session ID\n134: - **GIVEN** the GET response contains header `x-agentcube-session-id: abc-123`\n135: - **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` parses the response\n136: - **THEN** it SHALL return `\"abc-123\"`\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: Bootstrap missing session header\n139: - **GIVEN** the GET response does not contain `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n140: - **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` processes the response\n141: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")`\n142: \n143: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Invoke\n144: \n145: The system SHALL send POST requests to the invocation base URL with session headers and JSON payload.\n146: \n147: #### Scenario: Invoke via POST\n148: - **GIVEN** a valid `session_id` and `payload`\n149: - **WHEN** `invoke(session_id, payload)` is called\n150: - **THEN** it SHALL send `POST` to `self.base_url` with headers `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` and `Content-Type: application/json`, and body as JSON-serialized `payload`\n151: \n152: #### Scenario: Invoke timeout tuple\n153: - **GIVEN** `invoke` is called with `timeout=None`\n154: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n155: - **THEN** the timeout SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` tuple\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: Invoke with explicit timeout\n158: - **GIVEN** `invoke` is called with `timeout=60.0`\n159: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n160: - **THEN** the timeout SHALL be `(connect_timeout, 60.0)` tuple\n161: \n162: #### Scenario: Invoke response return\n163: - **GIVEN** the POST request completes\n164: - **WHEN** `invoke` finishes\n165: - **THEN** it SHALL return the `requests.Response` object without parsing\n166: \n167: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Base URL\n168: \n169: The system SHALL construct the invocation base URL from router URL, namespace, and agent name.\n170: \n171: #### Scenario: Base URL construction\n172: - **GIVEN** `router_url`, `namespace`, and `agent_name`\n173: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` initializes\n174: - **THEN** `base_url` SHALL be `urljoin(router_url, f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\")`\n175: \n176: ### Requirement: Session Header Management\n177: \n178: The system SHALL use the session header `x-agentcube-session-id` for all Agent Runtime data plane requests.\n179: \n180: #### Scenario: Session header constant\n181: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class\n182: - **WHEN** accessing `SESSION_HEADER`\n183: - **THEN** it SHALL equal `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n184: \n185: #### Scenario: Session header on invoke request\n186: - **GIVEN** `invoke(session_id, payload)` is called\n187: - **WHEN** the POST request is constructed\n188: - **THEN** the request SHALL include header `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: Session header on bootstrap GET\n191: - **GIVEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n192: - **WHEN** the GET request is constructed\n193: - **THEN** the request SHALL use the session default headers only (no explicit session header needed for bootstrap)\n194: \n195: ### Requirement: HTTP Client Configuration\n196: \n197: The system SHALL configure the HTTP client with appropriate connection pooling and timeout defaults.\n198: \n199: #### Scenario: Data plane session configuration\n200: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is initialized\n201: - **WHEN** the session is created\n202: - **THEN** it SHALL have `HTTPAdapter` mounted with `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`\n203: \n204: #### Scenario: Default timeouts\n205: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is initialized without timeout arguments\n206: - **WHEN** any request is made\n207: - **THEN** the timeout tuple SHALL be `(5.0, 120)` (connect_timeout, read_timeout)\n208: \n209: ### Requirement: Logging\n210: \n211: The system SHALL provide configurable logging for `AgentRuntimeClient` operations.\n212: \n213: #### Scenario: Verbose logging enabled\n214: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is constructed with `verbose=True`\n215: - **WHEN** operations are performed\n216: - **THEN** the logger SHALL output debug-level messages\n217: \n218: #### Scenario: Default logging level\n219: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is constructed with `verbose=False` (default)\n220: - **WHEN** operations are performed\n221: - **THEN** the logger SHALL output at `INFO` level or higher\n222: \n223: ## File Changes\n224: \n225: | Action | File | Description |\n226: |--------|------|-------------|\n227: | Create | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` class with context manager support |\n228: | Create | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` for Agent Runtime data plane |\n\n(End of file - total 228 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-028: SDK AgentRuntimeClient — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `sdk-python`\n- **Language:** Python\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntimeClient Initialization\n\nThe system SHALL construct an `AgentRuntimeClient` that resolves configuration from arguments and environment variables, bootstraps a session ID via the data plane, and initializes the underlying `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`.\n\n#### Scenario: Constructor with all arguments\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is constructed with explicit `agent_name`, `namespace`, `router_url`, `verbose`, `session_id`, `timeout`, and `connect_timeout`\n- **WHEN** the constructor completes\n- **THEN** all instance fields (`agent_name`, `namespace`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`, `logger`, `router_url`, `session_id`) SHALL be set to the provided values\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775869646617,"end":1775869646625}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869647924,"sessionID":"ses_285ebdaa6ffeX26M0sdERuF1ux","part":{"id":"prt_d7a1457a8001dLKNfnwaqwTq3g","messageID":"msg_d7a143e2f0017GYtC712NcPoqE","sessionID":"ses_285ebdaa6ffeX26M0sdERuF1ux","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_013bd1ceee904d52b922567c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-028/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-028/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient — Tasks\n2: \n3: > **Module:** sdk-python\n4: > **Language:** Python\n5: > **Size:** M\n6: > **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n7: > **Reference:** `changes/AR-028/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-028/design.md`, `changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md`\n8: > **Dependency:** AR-027 (SDK CodeInterpreterClient — shared utilities, exceptions, scaffolding)\n9: \n10: ---\n11: \n12: ## T-1: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient — Base URL and HTTP session\n13: \n14: - [ ] Verify `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.__init__` constructs `base_url` via `urljoin(router_url, f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\")`\n15: - [ ] Verify `SESSION_HEADER` class constant equals `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n16: - [ ] Verify session is created via `create_session()` with `HTTPAdapter(pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10)`\n17: - [ ] Verify default `timeout=120` and `connect_timeout=5.0` are stored\n18: - [ ] Write test: `base_url` is correctly constructed from `router_url`, `namespace`, `agent_name`\n19: - [ ] Write test: `SESSION_HEADER` equals `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n20: - [ ] Write test: session has `HTTPAdapter` with `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`\n21: - [ ] Write test: constructor stores all fields correctly with explicit arguments\n22: - [ ] Write test: constructor uses default `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`\n23: \n24: **Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_data_plane_client\"`\n25: \n26: ---\n27: \n28: ## T-2: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient — bootstrap_session_id\n29: \n30: - [ ] Verify `bootstrap_session_id()` sends `GET` to `self.base_url`\n31: - [ ] Verify `bootstrap_session_id()` reads `x-agentcube-session-id` header from response\n32: - [ ] Verify `bootstrap_session_id()` raises `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")` when header is absent\n33: - [ ] Verify `bootstrap_session_id()` calls `resp.raise_for_status()`\n34: - [ ] Write test: `bootstrap_session_id()` returns session ID when header is present\n35: - [ ] Write test: `bootstrap_session_id()` raises `ValueError` when header is missing\n36: - [ ] Write test: `bootstrap_session_id()` raises `HTTPError` on non-2xx response\n37: \n38: **Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_bootstrap_session\"`\n39: \n40: ---\n41: \n42: ## T-3: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient — invoke\n43: \n44: - [ ] Verify `invoke(session_id, payload)` sends `POST` to `self.base_url`\n45: - [ ] Verify request includes header `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n46: - [ ] Verify request includes header `Content-Type: application/json`\n47: - [ ] Verify request body is JSON-serialized `payload`\n48: - [ ] Verify timeout defaults to `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` when `timeout=None`\n49: - [ ] Verify timeout is `(connect_timeout, timeout)` when explicit `timeout` is provided\n50: - [ ] Verify `invoke()` returns `requests.Response` object without parsing\n51: - [ ] Verify `invoke()` calls `resp.raise_for_status()`\n52: - [ ] Write test: `invoke()` POSTs correct URL with session header and JSON body\n53: - [ ] Write test: `invoke()` with `timeout=None` uses default read timeout `120`\n54: - [ ] Write test: `invoke()` with `timeout=60.0` uses read timeout `60.0`\n55: - [ ] Write test: `invoke()` returns raw `requests.Response`\n56: \n57: **Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_data_plane_invoke\"`\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: ## T-4: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient — close\n62: \n63: - [ ] Verify `close()` calls `self.session.close()`\n64: - [ ] Write test: `close()` closes the underlying HTTP session without error\n65: - [ ] Write test: `close()` is idempotent (safe to call multiple times)\n66: \n67: **Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_data_plane_close\"`\n68: \n69: ---\n70: \n71: ## T-5: AgentRuntimeClient — Initialization with defaults\n72: \n73: - [ ] Verify `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` stores `agent_name`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`\n74: - [ ] Verify `router_url` is resolved from arg or `ROUTER_URL` env var\n75: - [ ] Verify `ValueError` is raised when neither `router_url` arg nor `ROUTER_URL` env is set\n76: - [ ] Verify `dp_client` is constructed as `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` with resolved params\n77: - [ ] Write test: constructor with only `agent_name` uses all defaults\n78: - [ ] Write test: constructor with explicit args stores all fields correctly\n79: - [ ] Write test: constructor resolves `router_url` from `ROUTER_URL` env var\n80: - [ ] Write test: constructor raises `ValueError` when no `router_url` available\n81: \n82: **Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_client_init_defaults\"`\n83: \n84: ---\n85: \n86: ## T-6: AgentRuntimeClient — Session bootstrapping and reuse\n87: \n88: - [ ] Verify when `session_id=None`, constructor calls `dp_client.bootstrap_session_id()` and stores result\n89: - [ ] Verify when `session_id` is provided, constructor does NOT call `bootstrap_session_id()`\n90: - [ ] Verify logger is created via `get_logger()` with `level=\"DEBUG\"` if `verbose=True`, else `\"INFO\"`\n91: - [ ] Write test: `session_id=None` triggers bootstrap and stores returned session ID\n92: - [ ] Write test: `session_id=\"existing-id\"` skips bootstrap and uses provided value\n93: - [ ] Write test: `verbose=True` creates logger with DEBUG level\n94: - [ ] Write test: `verbose=False` (default) creates logger with INFO level\n95: \n96: **Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_client_session\"`\n97: \n98: ---\n99: \n100: ## T-7: AgentRuntimeClient — Context manager\n101: \n102: - [ ] Verify `__enter__()` returns `self`\n103: - [ ] Verify `__exit__(exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb)` calls `close()`\n104: - [ ] Verify `__exit__` does NOT suppress exceptions (returns `None` or `False`)\n105: - [ ] Write test: `__enter__` returns `self`\n106: - [ ] Write test: `__exit__` with no exception calls `close()`\n107: - [ ] Write test: `__exit__` with exception calls `close()` and re-raises exception\n108: \n109: **Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_context_manager\"`\n110: \n111: ---\n112: \n113: ## T-8: AgentRuntimeClient — invoke\n114: \n115: - [ ] Verify `invoke(payload)` validates `session_id` is truthy; raises `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")` if falsy\n116: - [ ] Verify `invoke(payload)` calls `dp_client.invoke(session_id, payload, timeout)`\n117: - [ ] Verify `invoke(payload)` returns `resp.json()` (parsed JSON, not raw response)\n118: - [ ] Verify `invoke(payload, timeout=30.0)` passes `timeout=30.0` to data plane\n119: - [ ] Verify `invoke(payload, timeout=None)` passes `timeout=None` to data plane (data plane uses default)\n120: - [ ] Write test: `invoke()` with valid session calls `dp_client.invoke()` and returns parsed JSON\n121: - [ ] Write test: `invoke()` with `session_id=None` raises `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n122: - [ ] Write test: `invoke()` with `timeout=30.0` passes timeout to data plane\n123: - [ ] Write test: `invoke()` with `timeout=None` passes `None` to data plane\n124: \n125: **Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_client_invoke\"`\n126: \n127: ---\n128: \n129: ## T-9: AgentRuntimeClient — close\n130: \n131: - [ ] Verify `close()` calls `dp_client.close()`\n132: - [ ] Write test: `close()` delegates to `dp_client.close()`\n133: - [ ] Write test: `close()` is idempotent (safe to call multiple times)\n134: \n135: **Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_client_close\"`\n136: \n137: ---\n138: \n139: ## T-10: Integration tests\n140: \n141: - [ ] Write integration test: full lifecycle with context manager (init → bootstrap → invoke → cleanup)\n142: - [ ] Write integration test: pre-provisioned session skips bootstrap\n143: - [ ] Write integration test: invoke with custom timeout\n144: - [ ] Write integration test: context manager exit with exception still closes session\n145: - [ ] Write integration test: missing `ROUTER_URL` raises `ValueError`\n146: \n147: **Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_agent_runtime_integration\"`\n148: \n149: ---\n150: \n151: ## T-11: Lint, type-check, coverage gate\n152: \n153: - [ ] `ruff check python-sdk/agentcube/` — no violations\n154: - [ ] `mypy python-sdk/agentcube/` — no type errors\n155: - [ ] `pytest python-sdk/tests/ -v` — all pass\n156: - [ ] `pytest python-sdk/tests/ --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing` — coverage ≥ 80%\n157: \n158: **Verification:** Run all lint/typecheck/coverage commands\n159: \n160: ---\n161: \n162: ## Dependency Graph\n163: \n164: ```\n165: T-1 ──┬── T-2\n166:       ├── T-3\n167:       └── T-4\n168: \n169: T-5 ──┬── T-6 ──┬── T-7\n170:       │         ├── T-8\n171:       │         └── T-9\n172:       │\n173:       └── (depends on T-1, T-2, T-3, T-4 for AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient)\n174: \n175: T-10 ── (T-6, T-7, T-8, T-9)\n176: \n177: T-11 ── (all above)\n178: ```\n179: \n180: ## Parallelizable Groups\n181: \n182: | Group | Tasks | Prerequisites |\n183: |-------|-------|---------------|\n184: | G1 | T-1 | None |\n185: | G2 | T-2, T-3, T-4 | T-1 |\n186: | G3 | T-5 | T-1 (AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient exists) |\n187: | G4 | T-6, T-7, T-8, T-9 | T-5, T-2, T-3, T-4 |\n188: | G5 | T-10 | T-6, T-7, T-8, T-9 |\n189: | G6 | T-11 | All above |\n190: \n191: ---\n192: \n193: ## Acceptance Criteria\n194: \n195: | # | Criterion | Command |\n196: |---|-----------|---------|\n197: | AC1 | `AgentRuntimeClient` can be imported from `agentcube` | `python -c \"from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\"` |\n198: | AC2 | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` can be imported from `agentcube.clients` | `python -c \"from agentcube.clients import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"` |\n199: | AC3 | Constructor resolves config from args and env vars | `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_client_init_defaults\"` |\n200: | AC4 | Session bootstrap via GET works | `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_bootstrap_session\"` |\n201: | AC5 | Session reuse with provided `session_id` works | `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_client_session\"` |\n202: | AC6 | Context manager lifecycle works | `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_context_manager\"` |\n203: | AC7 | Invoke with payload and timeout works | `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_client_invoke\"` |\n204: | AC8 | Invoke without session raises `ValueError` | `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_client_invoke\"` |\n205: | AC9 | Close is idempotent | `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_client_close\"` |\n206: | AC10 | Data plane base URL construction is correct | `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_data_plane_client\"` |\n207: | AC11 | Data plane invoke sends correct headers and body | `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_data_plane_invoke\"` |\n208: | AC12 | Coverage ≥ 80% | `pytest tests/ --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing` |\n\n(End of file - total 208 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient — Tasks\n\n> **Module:** sdk-python\n> **Language:** Python\n> **Size:** M\n> **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n> **Reference:** `changes/AR-028/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-028/design.md`, `changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md`\n> **Dependency:** AR-027 (SDK CodeInterpreterClient — shared utilities, exceptions, scaffolding)\n\n---\n\n## T-1: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient — Base URL and HTTP session\n\n- [ ] Verify `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.__init__` constructs `base_url` via `urljoin(router_url, f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\")`\n- [ ] Verify `SESSION_HEADER` class constant equals `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n- [ ] Verify session is created via `create_session()` with `HTTPAdapter(pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10)`\n- [ ] Verify default `timeout=120` and `connect_timeout=5.0` are stored\n- [ ] Write test: `base_url` is correctly constructed from `router_url`, `namespace`, `agent_name`\n- [ ] Write test: `SESSION_HEADER` equals `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n- [ ] Write test: session has `HTTPAdapter` with `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-028/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775869647916,"end":1775869647922}}}}
